OL,3,CLabour blame game begins as Plaid
OL,4,CCymru poised to lead Wales
OL,6,FThis morning, Wales is waking up to
OL,7,Fsomething it has never known.
OL,9,FFor more than a quarter of a century,
OL,10,FWelsh Labour has been the natural
OL,11,Fparty of government. Since devolution
OL,12,Fin 1999 it has led every
OL,13,Fadministration in Cardiff Bay, and its
OL,14,Fdominance stretches back a century.
OL,16,FLess than four years ago, senior Welsh
OL,17,FLabour figures were celebrating what
OL,18,Fthen First Minister Mark Drakeford
OL,19,Fcalled "an extraordinary and
OL,20,Funrivalled record of electoral
OL,21,Fsuccess".
OL,26,@{D@HOU}D@HO]
