OL,3,CLabour blame game begins as Plaid
OL,4,CCymru poised to lead Wales
OL,6,FThe irony this morning is how quickly
OL,7,Fthat dominance has unravelled.
OL,9,FInside Labour, the recriminations have
OL,10,Falready begun.
OL,12,FFormer Blaenau Gwent MS Alun Davies,
OL,13,Fwho lost his seat yesterday, told
OL,14,FChannel 4 News the blame lay squarely
OL,15,Fwith Keir Starmer and the Labour Party
OL,16,Fin London, accusing the Prime Minister
OL,17,Fof showing "disregard" for Wales.
OL,19,FBut others inside the party are
OL,20,Fpushing back hard against that
OL,21,Fanalysis.
OL,26,@yD@LOUyD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
